activityList.description: Stopped at the 3 mile to watch a buck scraping a tree. Probably 20 yards from the trail.
3 hills.

Out and back route on the trail. I think the course was a bit long. The pace doesnt work out otherwise. Garmin had 5K at 18:27, Strava at 18:28. Averaged 5:55/mile. Strava also had 11:52 for two miles, 5:51 for the fastest mile.
Helped a guy push his car. Hardest part of the run. 3 moderate hills.
Legs were tired today.
Warm up then on the track. 800m at 2:47. 3 x 1200m at 4:19, 4:19, 4:18. 1 x 400m at 77 seconds. Cool down.
Hills 0.15 miles x 4. 4:30 - 5:10/mile.
Never looked at my watch. Felt tired and slow.
Cool down
Warm up.
4 miles, changed into flats. 3 hills, jog between.
Im not sure why 6 miles often seems to go better than 4. 6:56, 6;34, 6:35, 6:30, 6:25, 6:32.
Humid. 6:32 for the middle mile. Still testing the knees.
30 miles for the week.
Farthest run in a long time. Wanted to give 15K a try.
The watch still works! 6:26s for the last 3 miles.
Almost 3.5 into a 4 miler I drifted into a chain-link fence. It stripped the face off my watch. I carried it home. A little work with a small screwdriver to reconnect it and it started working again.
Warmer than its been. I really started to feel it 2 miles in.
19:22 for 5K. 3rd mile was 6:07.
A week off because of vertigo. That felt surprisingly good.
19:23 5K, 39:56 10K. Windy. 14 mph and gusts from the NW.
First 5-miler Ive run since  who knows?
The 5th mile was 6:16.
Hot. Humidity makes it feel like 90 degrees.
Good. First day in shorts. 6:49, 6:29, 6:20, 6:18.
My watch didnt work.
Not sure why Garmin was so off. Ran the Grand Blue Mile. in 5:04.
Cool down.
6 x 400m with walk/jog rest. Between 72 and 76 seconds for 400m.
Warm up.
Out and back. 6 x 200m at low 5 minute pace with 200m jog between on the track.
A few build-ups the last mile.
This felt good.
Felt good. 6:38, 6:27, 6:21. Plan to test it out more this week.
Whoa windy! 27 out of the NW.
Felt ok today. My right calf felt pretty normal. Better than on my walk yesterday.

Kept it as slow as I could. My right calf started to tighten around 3/4 a mile and started to improve a little at 1.5 miles. Rolling and ice. If the weather hadnt been so warm I might have been in trouble.
Pulled my calf a little more than a mile into it. Stopped, walked. Limp-jogged home. Felt good otherwise.
Still not feeling great. Lots of mud and water on the trail.
Hilly and windy. I have been sick the last few days. I wasnt sure how this would go. Head felt funny when I left, eyes not really tracking, but better after a mile or so.
Coyote on the north trail. An eagle flew over the house when I finished.
The first mile felt a bit rusty after a few days off. Hip feels good.

At my turn around spot I saw a coyote out on the ice. On the way back I saw two bald eagles circling. They landed in a cottonwood tree just as I crossed under 86th. I stopped under it and watched I could hear the chirping at each other.
23 mph wind out of the WNW. 6 degrees with wind chill. Supposed to be a shake out but was not. More rest planned before spring.
That felt a little rough. Wind and cold on the way out. First run with ASICS 2000. Glad to be wearing them again.
19:24 for 5K. 6:37, 6:10, 6:10, 6:23. Nice to finally get a warmer day.
The wind was kind of brutal.
The north trail was dangerous. There was a light snow this morning so it was impossible to see what was ice and what was uneven. Windy.
19:44 for 5K. 40:12 for 10K. 6:44, 6:26, 6:27, 6:22, _6:14_, 6:36. The sidewalks are still pretty bad the first and last mile. The trails are better than earlier this week. Still need to be careful.
50 miles for January.
Cold. 9 degrees at the start. Slippery and uneven after some warm days earlier this week.
Trails are a little worse than yesterday. 33 degrees and sunny.

7:08, 6:42, 6:39, 6:41, 6:32, 6:42. We got 11 inches of snow two days ago. I wasnt sure if the trails would be clear. It turns out they were quite a bit better than the sidewalks. The snow crunched firmly under my feet where the crews had cleared. It was prettier the further west I ran, the snow turned everything into white, velvet mounds. The light of the sun became a radiant luminescence, diffused by the trees that lined the path like great white arbors.
40:45 for 10K. 6:42, 6:24, 6:27, 6:32, 6:20, 6:49. The 5th mile hurt and now I know why. I had to cut through snow and awkwardly cross a few streets in the last mile.
Cold. Tired.
6:17 the 3rd mile.
Right hip still bugging me.
Felt good. The trail was not as slippery as I expected. 6:55, 6:47, 6:39, 6:31.
Fresh snow, hilly, -4 degrees at the start, -20ish wind chill. Right hip is tight.
